    • Constructor Detail

      • AbiChromatogramBuilder

        public AbiChromatogramBuilder(String id)
        Create a new AbiChromatogramBuilder instance with all fields except for the id unset. In order to successfully build a valid AbiChromatogram object please use the various setter methods in this class to set everything before calling build().
        Parameters:
        id - the id for this Chromatogram object to have; can not be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if id is null.

      • AbiChromatogramBuilder

        public AbiChromatogramBuilder(String id,
                              File abiFile)
                       throws IOException
        Create a new AbiChromatogramBuilder instance with the given id and all fields initially set to the the values encoded in the given ab1 file.
        Parameters:
        id - the id for this Chromatogram object to have; can not be null.
        abiFile - a AB1 encoded file that contains the initial values that this builder should have; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the file or if the given file is not a valid ab1 encoded file.
        NullPointerException - if either field is null.

      • AbiChromatogramBuilder

        public AbiChromatogramBuilder(String id,
                              InputStream abiFileStream)
                       throws IOException
        Create a new AbiChromatogramBuilder instance with the given id and all fields initially set to the the values encoded in the given ab1 encoded inputStream. The InputStream will NOT be closed by this constructor, client code must close the stream themselves after returning from this method (preferably in a finally block).
        Parameters:
        id - the id for this Chromatogram object to have; can not be null.
        abiFileStream - a ab1 encoded InputStream that contains the initial values that this builder should have; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the file or if the InputStream does not contain valid ab1 encoded data.
        NullPointerException - if either field is null.
